<title>Introduction</title>
<screenshot>
  <screeninfo>Here's a screenshot of &krusader;</screeninfo>
  <mediaobject>
    <imageobject><imagedata fileref="krusader_title.png" format="PNG"/></imageobject>
    <imageobject><imagedata fileref="krusader_title.png" format="EPS"/></imageobject>
    <textobject><phrase>Krusader Logo</phrase></textobject>
  </mediaobject>
</screenshot>

<para>&krusader; is an advanced twin-panel (commander-style)
      file-manager for &kde; 3.2 (similar to <application>Midnight or Total Commander</application>)
      with many extras.</para>

<para>It provides all the file management features you could possibly want.
      Plus: extensive archive handling, mounted filesystem support, &FTP;,
      advanced search module, viewer/editor, directory synchronisation,
      file content comparisons, powerful batch renaming and much, much more.
      It supports the following archive formats: tar, zip, bzip2, gzip, rar, ace, arj, iso and rpm.
      It can handle other &kioslaves1_url; such as smb:// or fish://.
      It is (almost) completely customizable, very user friendly, fast
      and looks great on your desktop! :-)
      You should give it a try.</para>

<para>Thank you for using &krusader;.</para>

<para>
<itemizedlist>
<title>Features</title>
  <listitem>
     <para>Configurable &toolbar_lnk; and
     <link linkend="key_bindings">key-bindings</link>.</para>
  </listitem>
  <listitem><para>Full Ace, Arj, Bzip2, Gzip, Tar, Rpm, Rar, Zip support
  <link linkend="archives">support</link>.</para></listitem>
  <listitem>
      <para><link linkend="krusearcher">Advanced search module</link> that can search in archives.</para>
  </listitem>
        <listitem><para><link linkend="compare-dir">Directory comparison</link> and
                  <link linkend="view-menu">filtering</link>.</para></listitem>
   <listitem>
            <para><link linkend="panels">Quick view and Tree panels</link>.</para>
  </listitem>
        <listitem><para>&FTP;/SAMBA client with a <link linkend="remote-man">connection manager</link>
                   with SFTP/SCP support.</para>
        </listitem>
  <listitem><para>Opens a <link linkend="commands-menu">terminal</link> to the browsed
   path.</para></listitem>
  <listitem>
     <para>Optional embedded &termemu_lnk;.</para>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
      <para>Configurable <link linkend="bookman">bookmark</link> list (using BookMan, the bookmark
      manager).</para>
  </listitem>
  <listitem><para>Easy editing of <link linkend="file-menu">file permissions</link>.</para></listitem>
  <listitem><para>Shows the <link linkend="panels">effective permissions for the current
   user.</link>.</para></listitem>
  <listitem>
       <para><link linkend="calculate">Calculates occupied space</link> by marked files and
        folders.</para>
   </listitem>
  <listitem>
        <para>Internal <link linkend="krviewer">viewer and configurable editor.</link></para>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
         <para>Offers a &cmdline_lnk; capable of running something in a
         terminal with a single click of a button.</para>
   </listitem>
  <listitem>
       <para>Completely supports drag'n'drop: drag from &konqueror; straight into a .tar.gz file, from
       &krusader;'s panel into the trash-bin, the desktop or into &konqueror;!</para>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
       <para><link linkend="unpacking-archives">Packs (or unpacks) files</link> into a single archive
       of your choice without typing a single command.</para>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
       <para><link linkend="test-archive">Tests the integrity of archives.</link>.</para>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
       <para><link linkend="compare-files">Compare files by content</link> (via external diff program
        such as &kompare; or &xxdiff;).</para>
   </listitem>
        <listitem>
      <para>Fully <link linkend="konfig-general">mimetype-aware</link> (with or without magic!).</para>
  </listitem>
        <listitem>
      <para>Built-in Mount-Manager &mountman_lnk;.</para>
  </listitem>
        <listitem>
      <para><link linkend="multi_rename">Krename</link> support, a very powerful
                                external batch renamer for &kde; 3.x.</para>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
     <para>&foldertabs_lnk;.</para>
  </listitem>
</itemizedlist>
</para>

<para>
